main event: An airman at Holloman AFB in New Mexico observed a white, light object performing varied maneuvers in the sky on April 29, 1952.
interesting points: The object was observed for 1 hour.
The object's movements were described as 'varied'.
The report categorized the object as possibly a balloon or an aircraft.
The report does not contain any photographs of the observed object.
The report was part of Project Blue Book, a historic U.S. Air Force program that investigated unidentified flying objects (UFOs).
